Selectolax is a fast HTML5 parser with full CSS selector support.

It is written in Cython and uses the Lexbor engine (preferred) for
high-performance parsing. This port is built with only the Lexbor
backend and links against the system www/lexbor library.

Key features:
- Very fast HTML5 parsing (significantly faster than BeautifulSoup + lxml)
- Powerful CSS selectors (including :nth-child, :not(), :contains, etc.)
- Methods like .css(), .css_first(), .text(), .attributes, etc.
- Low memory usage and excellent performance for web scraping and HTML processing.

WWW: https://github.com/rushter/selectolax
